This indicates a VirtualBox source compatibility issue with your current RHEL 9.8 kernel (5.14.0-687.22.1.el9_8.x86_64), not a missing package issue.

Option 1 (Recommended): Boot the EL9.7 kernel

Since you still have the 5.14.0-611.26.1.el9_7 kernel installed, try booting into it.

Check the GRUB entries:

grubby --info=ALL

or

awk -F\' '$1=="menuentry " {print $2}' /boot/grub2/grub.cfg

Then set the EL9.7 kernel as default:

grubby --set-default /boot/vmlinuz-5.14.0-611.26.1.el9_7.x86_64
reboot

After reboot:

uname -r
sudo /sbin/vboxconfig

Option 2: Use a newer VirtualBox build

If you must stay on RHEL 9.8, install the latest Oracle VirtualBox package once Oracle releases a build compatible with this kernel.

One more thing I'd like to verify

Please run:

rpm -qi virtualbox

or

dnf repolist

I want to confirm which Oracle VirtualBox repository your RPM came from. If the RPM isn't the latest available from Oracle, upgrading to a newer build may resolve the issue.
